<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,735,948]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,810,836]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</emphasis>
The identity of this species is uncertain as the dissection of the only male specimen is missing the aedeagus. Only the male bears a museum 
<typeStatus box="[680,731,848,874]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
disc but the two female specimens could also be 
<typeStatus box="[1303,1405,848,874]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">syntypes</typeStatus>
as they bear identical data labels although also labelled from the Indian Museum.
</paragraph>
